.TH "xdr_count_write_chunks" 9 "xdr_count_write_chunks" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xdr_count_write_chunks \- Count number of Write chunks in Write list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" xdr_count_write_chunks
.BI "(struct svc_rdma_recv_ctxt *rctxt "  ","
.BI "__be32 *p "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rctxt" 12
Received header and decoding state
.IP "p" 12
start of an un-decoded Write list
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Before allocating anything, ensure the ingress Write list is
safe to use.

Return values:
true: Write list is valid. \fIrctxt\fP's xdr_stream is updated
to point to the first byte past the Write list, and
the number of Write chunks is in rc_write_pcl.cl_count.
false: Write list is corrupt. \fIrctxt\fP's xdr_stream is left
in an indeterminate state.
